  "claim_short": "1901.03306 Gluck Weber Almost Interior Points in Ordered Banach Spaces Example Sobolev spaces asks whether W^{k,p}(R^d) has almost interior or quasi-interior points. Full solution: for every k in N_0, 1 =1, the Gaussian u(x)=exp(-|x|^2) belongs to W^{k,p}, is positive everywhere, dominates every compactly supported smooth function up to a scalar on its compact support, and C_c-infinity(R^d) is dense in W^{k,p};...",
